==English==

===Verb===
'''to enliven''' ''(transitive)''

#To make somebody or something more [[lively]] or [[interesting]]
#*''The game was much enlivened when both teams scored within five minutes of each other''
#To make something [[brighter]], [[sprightly]] or more [[cheerful]]
#*''A few more pictures on the wall would enliven this room''
#To give [[life]], [[action]], or [[spirit]] to

